caption: Ordered delivery through ChowNow and everything was great. Excellent food (try the veggie nachos and the potato flautas!!), easy to navigate menu, followed my special request for no plastic ware or napkins, and smooth delivery. The food stayed fresh and crispy. Would totally recommend this place. Perfect for vegetarians and could easily be vegan with some special requests.
Food is so flavorful and fresh with tons of options for vegetarians. A go-to for takeout!

I’m sad to write this review ... I’ve been coming here for years, and I don’t know if it’s who the owners have hired or what exactly, but the quality of the food has decreased a lot over the years.  The last 3 times I’ve ordered, the food either made me ill or was just.... extremely bland. I’m sorry to say that I won’t be returning.
Great hole in the wall
I ordered the chicken enchiladas with red sauce, my very favorite Mexican dish. I was disappointed. The food was luke warm, the chicken chunky and chewy and the tortilla was tortilla was too doughy.

My go-to Mexican takeout spot. The food is so authentic and SO fresh. The corn tortillas are made by hand! The menu has a ton of options and everything I have tried is good, and as a vegetarian I am very appreciative that each section (tacos, soles, quesadillas, etc.) has at least one veggie option (usually more - abd all tasty!). My favorites are the chile relleno and the mushroom quesadilla, and I always get a horchata when I order.

Absolutely incredible Mexican food and I am not easy to please. Having family from East LA, I grew up exposed to a variety of Mexican cuisine. Too often, I find myself disappointed by what passes for Mexican food in NYC. Not this place. Never have I been disappointed by their choice of seasoning. I highly recommend exploring their menu as it's all delicious.

Absolutely phenomenal. I moved here from Los Angeles almost 8 years ago and haven’t found a spot that reminded me of home until tonight!  Tonight was my first night eating here, perfect experience. Kind staff, incredible food. Enjoy.
Nice food

I always walk past this place and see people coming in and out so I decided to try it. THE FOOD WAS SO GOOD. I got empanadas, a tostada, and a burrito. They were all amazing. Tasted really authentic and every bite was flavorful and delicious. I’ll definitely be coming back! The prices, portions, and staff were also great. I felt very safe COVID wise while ordering and waiting.
2x tamales, 2x tacos, and nachos from Taqueria Milear is a weekly household ritual.  This is a good restaurant, run by nice people. A+

Always excellent food. Big menu with great options for lunch and dinner. My favorite tacos are the al pastor that comes with pineapple and the really well cooked buche and lengua tacos. Also love the empanadas.

Update November 2020: I am not sure if the quality somehow changed when the menu was changed or something but when I tried this place again after a few month hiatus the other day, it wasn’t as great as I have known it to be when I wrote my original five star review (see below).  Absolutely phenomenal! The burrito was out of this world, and easily the best Mexican food I’ve had in nyc (which while not known for its Mexican food by any means still has some decent spots but Taqueria Milear blows them out of the water!)

Searching for a taco place in brooklyn near my in laws and this place came out in second, I go by reviews when anything I buy or with restaurants that will try for the first time. The hole in the wall got my, because most places that are small like this one are good and we weren't disappointed. It's true, it's small for just about 12 people in a very tight enclosure so be ready to know it could be empty or packed and nowhere to sit. The food was beyond delicious and very authentic flavor. If you love orchata you must try theirs. I'm not sure what could have happened with the person that left a bad review because the delivery took too long but while we were there there were deliveries non stop. I will say this, they have their only delivery personnel and there are also third party delivery services that went to pick up, so it's best if you do your homework on who to get to deliver for you. Lastly, they deliver with $13 minimum. Enjoy de give this little hole in the wall place a chance.
If you get the mole and fresh corn tortillas you’ll know this spot is legit. BYOB if you dine in, entire restaurant probably seats between 10-20 people.

Absolutely terrible service. Ordered a meal at 6:30, called to inquire about the delivery at 8:00 pm and they said they were waiting on a delivery guy. By 8:45 still had no delivery, when we called to inquire they said they delivered it.  We received no call, no buzz up to our apartment (even though they claimed they called 4 times and buzzed up multiple times), and their defense was that the delivery guy gave the food to someone who said it was their food.... without even checking to verify!!!  When they offered to remake it, they couldn’t even give an ETA because they were “busy” with other orders. So... we are at the back of the line because they messed up and had us waiting over 2 hours.  I would give zero stars if I could and would never order from here again, if I did I probably wouldn’t even get the food.

It was clean, friendly, and reasonably priced spot. The decorations there have it a lot of character. I had never had "crispy tortillas" before. I expected it to just be the tortillas I've always had, but toasted to be a little crispy. And it was, but it was different enough such that it became a culinary experience for me. I ordered something that had thin cut steak. The steak was waaay over cooked and MUCH Yoooo chewy. I almost couldn't eat it. Everything else on the dish was delicious though. If I came back, I would try their vegetarian options. Overall the food didn't blow me away -- I'm having a hard time getting past the steak. However, everything else about it seemed charming. I'll give it a second chance. I just wouldn't recommend the entrees with steak.
